## **ADDITIONAL TERMS FOR SharaSpot LONDON LIMITED**
The following additional terms apply **specifically to the SharaSpot project** and modify the conditions of use.

### **1. Trademark & Branding Restrictions**
- "SharaSpot," the SharaSpot logo, and all related trademarks are **owned by SharaSpot LONDON LIMITED**.
- Any **forked or modified version** of this software **must remove** all SharaSpot branding (name, logo, and API keys).
- You may **not market, advertise, or distribute** any modified version under the name "SharaSpot" or claim official affiliation.

### **2. API Access & Usage Restrictions**
- This software **is open-source, but the SharaSpot API is proprietary**.
- Use of the SharaSpot API **requires explicit approval** and compliance with the [SharaSpot API Terms of Use](https://SharaSpot.app/api-terms).
- Unauthorized attempts to connect to the SharaSpot API may result in termination of access.
- To request API access, users must register at [SharaSpot Developer Portal](https://SharaSpot.app/developers) and agree to API Terms.
- **SharaSpot reserves the right to suspend or revoke API keys** if the Licensee exceeds usage limits, violates API Terms, or engages in unauthorized commercial use.

### **3. Enterprise Version (Commercial License)**
- A **commercial license is required** for access to **AI-powered analytics, premium support, and enterprise features**.
- The commercial version includes **priority API access, advanced reporting, and custom business integrations**.
- For enterprise licensing inquiries, contact **sales@SharaSpot.app**.

### **4. Competitive Use Restrictions (Covered Under API Terms)**
- Competitive use restrictions are covered in the **SharaSpot API Terms of Use** rather than this license.
- A "competing EV charging service" includes any **marketplace, platform, or software** that provides a **peer-to-peer or B2B EV charging network** similar to SharaSpot.
- General-purpose energy or mapping applications that do not provide **monetized EV charger access** are **not considered competing services**.

### **5. License Enforcement**
- Failure to comply with these additional terms may result in **revocation of API access**, but not the open-source license.
- SharaSpot London Limited **reserves the right to monitor API usage** and take appropriate action against violations.

### **6. Disclaimer of Warranty & Limitation of Liability**
- The Software is provided “as-is” without warranty of any kind.
- SharaSpot London Limited shall not be liable for any **direct, indirect, or incidental damages** resulting from the use or inability to use the API or Enterprise services.

### **7. Contributions & Open-Source Submissions**
- We welcome contributions from developers worldwide. Contributions can include **bug fixes, new features, translations, and documentation improvements**.
- Contributors retain copyright to their submissions but **grant SharaSpot a non-exclusive, worldwide, irrevocable, royalty-free license** to use, modify, and distribute their contributions.
- Contributions must **not** include proprietary or third-party code **without explicit permission**.
- All contributors must follow the [SharaSpot Contributor Guidelines](https://SharaSpot.app/contributor-guidelines).

### **8. Governing Law & Dispute Resolution**
- This Agreement shall be governed by and construed under the laws of **England and Wales**.
